ndgain-id_infr_01-raw.def:
Description: An indication of the potential risk of hydropower generation capacity weighted by the importance of hydropower to one country, i.e. the proportion of the electricity production from hydroelectric sources. The data of the projected change are available at the sub-continental level, drawn from (Hamududu & Killingtveit, 2012). 
Rationale: Due to the hydrological impact of climate change in the mid- to long- term (see the two exposure indicators in the water sector), climate change also is projected to directly impact hydropower generation capacity (Schaeffer et al., 2012). Calculation: The projected change is the percent change in the hydropower generation capacity from the historical baseline (2005) to the future projection (2050), using the A1B emission scenario.
ndgain-id_infr_01-raw.name: Projected change of hydropower generation capacity
